# Phaser 3 Patterns

## Scene Lifecycle
Follow Phaser's standard scene methods — don't reinvent the wheel:
- `init(data)` — receive data from previous scene
- `preload()` — load assets (sprites, audio, tilemaps)
- `create()` — set up game objects, physics, input handlers
- `update(time, delta)` — game loop, keep lightweight

## Scene Organization
- One scene per file: `MenuScene.ts`, `GameScene.ts`, `HUDScene.ts`
- Scenes own their display objects; shared state goes in a registry or manager
- Use `this.scene.launch()` for parallel scenes (e.g. HUD overlay)
- Pass data between scenes via `this.scene.start("Next", { data })`

## Game Objects
- Extend `Phaser.GameObjects.*` for custom entities, not raw classes
- Use object pools (`this.add.group()`) for frequently spawned objects (particles, tiles)
- Prefer `setOrigin(0.5)` for center-anchored objects

## Input
- Use Phaser's input system, not raw DOM events
- `this.input.on("pointerdown", handler)` for click/tap
- Clean up listeners in `shutdown()` to prevent leaks

## Asset Loading
- Load assets in a dedicated `PreloadScene`, not scattered across scenes
- Use texture atlases over individual sprites when possible
- Audio: load multiple formats for cross-browser (mp3 + ogg)

## Common Patterns

```typescript
// ✅ Object pool for tiles
const tileGroup = this.add.group({
  classType: TileSprite,
  maxSize: 500,
  runChildUpdate: true,
});

// ✅ Scene transition with data
this.scene.start("GameScene", { playerCount: 10, mapSize: 64 });

// ✅ Clean input cleanup
shutdown() {
  this.input.off("pointerdown");
  this.events.off("update");
}
```

## Don't Reinvent
- Use `Phaser.Math` for vectors, interpolation, random — don't write your own
- Use `Phaser.Tilemaps` for grid-based maps
- Use `Phaser.Tweens` for animations, not manual lerping
- Use `Phaser.Time.TimerEvent` for delays, not `setTimeout`
